The O's are at 46 as of the All Star break, with a .500 winning percentage (holy crap!). They play 11 more games. So 51 or 52 would be base rate. 58 is now impossible and so is fewer than 41. Losing all of the games between now and Aug 1 is pretty unlikely.

After July 15th loss to TB, there 13 games remain with the Orioles record standing at 45 wins and 45 losses (an even .500 record). 9 of the 13 remaining games remaining are against teams with a winning record. Those winning teams are the Yankees and Rays, who the Orioles have played 22 times, accumulating 8 wins ( a .363 winning percentage). However, 7 of those 9 games (and 7 of the 13 overall) are at home, where the Orioles have won nearly 60% of their games. considering the team's record at home as well as record against similar opponents, strength of schedule over these 13 remaining games, and recent performance of the upcoming opponents, I project even odds that the team wins more games than it loses over the next 13 to fall into either bucket C or D, and assign 0% probability of winning only 1 of 13 (bucket B) or more than 13 (bucket E).
Will they ever lose again!!!

The current winrate (50%) would suggest a 70/30 split between the 3rd and 4th bins, but I expect it to be slightly lower in the last games as they are facing somewhat stronger opponents (e.g. 3 games vs the NYY).

currently have won 43 games (rules out bucket a); currently on an 8 game win streak which reduces likelihood of bucket 2; 15 games remaining until the end of the month (which rules out bucket 5 because there will only be 58 games total); current W/L right now is about 50/50 - so with 16 games remaining (incl of the 1 aug game), 8 wins/8 loses presumptive stats - which would mean 51 wins;

Time is slipping just fast enough that despite the relatively "impressive" run as of late, I think the odds shift toward the central bins. I'm a little more biased toward the last two bins while the crowd median - "better than average" - grasps tightly on bin: 3 "Between 47 and 52."
